President Barack Obama has announced his nominations for three senior positions in the Treasury Department. Neal S. Wolin has been nominated for Deputy Secretary of the Treasury, Lael Brainard has been nominated for Under Secretary of the Treasury for International Affairs, and Stuart A. Levey will remain in his position as Under Secretary for Terrorism and Financial Intelligence. These nominations fill three of the four most senior Senate-confirmed positions in the Treasury Department. President Obama expressed his confidence in these individuals and their ability to serve the American people under the leadership of Secretary Geithner.